Shortly before #soberoctober began, Wizards of the Coast announced their upcoming digital game &ldquo;Magic: The Gathering Arena.&rdquo;
I have fond childhood memories of playing Magic with my brother. Our first experience was with &ldquo;Portal&rdquo;, a starter set that came with enough cards for both of us to experiment with deckbuilding and learn the rules. After that we played throughout Odyssey, Onslaught and Mirrodin blocks, or approximately 2000-2006.
Then I got a computer with a graphics card, went to college, and video games effectively replaced Magic for me.
